{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Match US transparency by releasing all existing UAP records",
        "additional_details": "Following recent declassification efforts in the United States, we call on the UK Government to release all records, sensor data, and witness reports held by the Ministry of Defence regarding Unidentified Anomalous Phenomena (UAP). Since the closure of the 'UFO Desk' in 2009, the public has been told there is no threat, yet we [want to...] believe air safety and national security concerns remain. We demand transparency to ensure public trust and scientific progress.",
